### Workshop quick-start
# Use the VS Code "REST Client" extension (or compatible .http support).
# Start the app first:
# dotnet run --launch-profile http

@host = http://localhost:5000
@contentType = application/json

### Root UI
GET {{host}}/

### OpenAPI document
GET {{host}}/openapi/v1.json

### List current famous people
GET {{host}}/api/famouspeople
Accept: {{contentType}}

### Create a new famous person
# @name createPerson
POST {{host}}/api/famouspeople
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

{
  "fullName": "Grace Hopper",
  "background": "American computer scientist and U.S. Navy rear admiral who helped pioneer compilers and popularized machine-independent programming languages.",
  "competenceField": "Computer Science",
  "headshotUrl": "https://ui-avatars.com/api/?name=Grace+Hopper&size=256"
}

### Capture created id for follow-up requests
@createdPersonId = {{createPerson.response.body.$.id}}

### Update the person created above
PUT {{host}}/api/famouspeople/{{createdPersonId}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "id": "{{createdPersonId}}",
  "fullName": "Grace Hopper",
  "background": "American computer scientist and U.S. Navy rear admiral whose work on compilers and COBOL helped shape modern software development.",
  "competenceField": "Computer Science",
  "headshotUrl": "https://ui-avatars.com/api/?name=Grace+Hopper&size=256"
}

### Update only headshot for a person
PUT {{host}}/api/famouspeople/{{createdPersonId}}/headshot
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

{
  "headshotUrl": "https://example.com/images/grace.jpg"
}

### Confirm the updated list
GET {{host}}/api/famouspeople
Accept: {{contentType}}

### Example validation failure
POST {{host}}/api/famouspeople
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

{
  "fullName": "",
  "background": "This should fail because fullName is required.",
  "competenceField": "Workshop Demo"
}

### Example not-found update
PUT {{host}}/api/famouspeople/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

{
  "id": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "fullName": "Missing Person",
  "background": "This demonstrates the 404 response for an unknown identifier.",
  "competenceField": "Workshop Demo"
}
